Lastly, the phrase "jibu lako halina neno lingine lolote" can be interpreted using multiple interpretations, depending on its context. If it were to mean "Why are you taking their picture", "jibu" would be a colloquial form of asking why, "lako" can mean "their" (referring to the people in the photo), and "neno" can be as an informal form of "kids" or "children." Finally, "lingine" can mean "them" or "their" and "lolote" can be interpreted as an emphatic form of "are seeing the same child twice in a single photo?" or "are you photographing the people together?"
